Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:05.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:05.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你好 我是斯科特-曼利
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.84,0:00:09.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Today I want to talk to you about weapons grade stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.84,0:00:09.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,今天我想和你谈谈武器级的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:13.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now the term weapons grade has entered into popular power lines to the extent
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.36,0:00:13.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 "武器级 "一词已经进入了流行的权力线 以至于我们目前正在谈论针对华尔街的武器级备忘录
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:18.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that we are currently talking about weapons grade memes being deployed against Wall Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:18.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们目前正在讨论针对华尔街部署的武器级备忘录
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.03,0:00:23.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna point out that you should not confuse this with military grade
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.03,0:00:23.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我想指出的是 你不应该将其与军事级别相混淆
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.27,0:00:25.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is a completely meaningless term
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.27,0:00:25.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是一个完全没有意义的术语
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.39,0:00:29.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,generally added to Amazon listings to sell them to a certain type of person.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.39,0:00:29.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,一般是加在亚马逊的清单上 以卖给某类人
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:35.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now weapons grade refers to weapons-grade material needed to make nuclear weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.08,0:00:35.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 武器级是指制造核武器所需的武器级材料
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:42.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And these basically set down constraints as to the isotope ratios for the material
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:42.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这些材料基本上对材料的同位素比例作出了限制
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.55,0:00:45.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so that they can be used to easily build bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.55,0:00:45.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以便它们可以被用来轻易地制造炸弹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:48.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the reason why of course we're interested in this is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:48.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然 我们对此感兴趣的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.94,0:00:54.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,you want to keep that kind of material under control to stop it to stop nuclear proliferation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.94,0:00:54.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你想把这种材料控制住 以阻止它来阻止核扩散
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.21,0:01:01.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now the origin of these terms I believe goes back to like the 1950s
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.21,0:01:01.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 这些术语的起源我相信可以追溯到20世纪50年代
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.10,0:01:06.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,where the US is starting to collaborate on nuclear science with other nations
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.10,0:01:06.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,美国开始与其他国家在核科学方面进行合作
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.55,0:01:10.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and they're looking at what level of uranium enrichment they can share
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.55,0:01:10.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们正在研究他们可以分享何种程度的铀浓缩
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.99,0:01:14.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and there's this document that was published that figured out that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.99,0:01:14.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并有这样的文件 被公布 认为
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.39,0:01:18.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,for research reactors they shouldn't allow anything more than 20%
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.39,0:01:18.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,对于研究反应堆 他们不应该允许超过20％的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.59,0:01:24.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so 20% becomes the transition from low enriched uranium to highly enriched uranium.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.59,0:01:24.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 20%成为低浓缩铀到高浓缩铀的过渡
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.51,0:01:26.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And weapons grade is like 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.51,0:01:26.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而武器级是80%
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.43,0:01:30.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Yeah depending upon the material, you've got different rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.43,0:01:30.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,是的 根据材料的不同 你有不同的规则
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.36,0:01:35.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,For uranium it's all about the isotopic ratio of uranium-235
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.36,0:01:35.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,对于铀 它是所有关于铀235的同位素比率
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.93,0:01:39.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is the stuff that actually explodes and drives the chain reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.93,0:01:39.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是实际爆炸和驱动链式反应的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.74,0:01:45.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and uranium-238 which sort of generally sits on the sidelines and doesn't do very much useful stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.74,0:01:45.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,和铀-238的同位素比例 后者通常坐在一边 不做非常有用的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:57.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now in nature you've only got 0.7% uranium-235 in regular uranium and the rest is 99.3% uranium-238
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:57.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 在自然界中 普通铀中只有0.7%的铀235 其余的是99.3%的铀238
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.93,0:02:03.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so it is possible to make a nuclear reactor using just this regular material
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.93,0:02:03.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 它是可能的 使一个核反应堆只用这种普通的材料
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.96,0:02:07.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but you have to have a lot of moderators to slow down the neutrons
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.96,0:02:07.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但你必须有大量的调节器 以减缓中子的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.50,0:02:13.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and get them to pay attention to the 235 and stop all those 238s from getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.50,0:02:13.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并让它们注意到235 阻止所有这些238进入的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:17.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But if you go through a process of enrichment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:17.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是 如果你通过一个浓缩的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.03,0:02:21.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,where you exploit the very small differences in mass between these two atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.03,0:02:21.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你利用这两种原子之间非常小的质量差异
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.33,0:02:27.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you enhance the concentration of the uranium-235
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.33,0:02:27.42,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且你提高了铀235的浓度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.80,0:02:31.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,then your reaction gets easier and easier to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.80,0:02:31.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那么你的反应就会变得越来越容易进行
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:35.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now for the first atom bomb drop from a plane that was a little boy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.54,0:02:35.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 第一颗原子弹从飞机上投下 是一个小男孩
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:40.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it was made with material that was on average 80% enriched.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:40.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它是用平均80%的浓缩材料制成的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:44.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I say on average because apparently large parts of it were 90% enriched
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:44.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我说平均 因为很明显 它的很大一部分是90%的浓缩物
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:47.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but there was some part which was only 50% enriched.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:47.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但也有一些部分只有50%的浓缩度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:52.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,A lot of these details are uh still somewhat classified.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:52.67,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这些细节在某种程度上仍然是保密的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:58.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So it's relatively easy to make an atom bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:58.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 制造原子弹是比较容易的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:03:05.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,if you have enough for uranium at 80 concentration enrichment, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:03:05.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,如果你有足够的浓缩度为80的铀 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:12.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,As you get to lower and lower levels of enrichment you need larger and larger critical masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:12.33,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当你达到越来越低的浓缩水平时 你需要越来越大的临界质量
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:19.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And like in theory I believe you can make 20% low enriched uranium go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:19.23,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,就像在理论上 我相信你可以使20%的低浓缩铀爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:25.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The point is that you you want to restrict these very high things from being available to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:25.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,问题是 你想限制这些非常高的东西被提供给世界
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:32.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and generally the only stuff that's really kept around these days is highly enriched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:32.99,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且一般来说 现在唯一真正保留的东西是高浓缩的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:37.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The highly enriched uranium is used in very limited number of cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:37.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,高浓缩铀被用于非常有限的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:41.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Sometimes used in submarine reactors for example
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:41.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有时用于潜艇反应堆 例如
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.48,0:03:46.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,where you want to get high power density and the least amount of stuff getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.48,0:03:46.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在那里你想获得高功率密度和最少的东西得到的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.22,0:03:51.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Okay so plutonium.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.22,0:03:51.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,好吧 那么钚
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:55.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now plutonium is actually what's used in most atom bombs these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:55.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 钚实际上是现在大多数原子弹中使用的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:56.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:56.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它好得多
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:03:59.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It has much lower critical mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:03:59.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它的临界质量低得多
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:02.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's a lot harder to work with for various reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:02.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,由于各种原因 它更难处理
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.54,0:04:04.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But it's generally become the thing of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.54,0:04:04.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但它通常成为首选的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.70,0:04:07.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now plutonium isn't a natural material.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.70,0:04:07.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 钚并不是一种天然材料
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:08.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's made in a reactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:08.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它是在反应堆中制造的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:13.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's actually made where you have a regular chain reaction going with uranium-235
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:13.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它实际上是在你有一个常规的连锁反应与铀235
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:16.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and that uranium-238 that isn't doing anything useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:16.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,和铀-238 没有做任何有用的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.52,0:04:20.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It will frequently absorb a neutron that will increase the mass to 239
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.52,0:04:20.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将经常吸收一个中子 将质量增加到239
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:25.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then it'll undergo a series of radioactive decays and you'll get plutonium-239.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:25.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后 它将经历一系列的放射性衰变 你会得到钚239
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.97,0:04:29.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So this is how they made the plutonium for the first atom bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.97,0:04:29.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这就是他们为第一颗原子弹制造钚的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:32.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They built these reactors that didn't produce power.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:32.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们建立了这些反应堆 不生产电力
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:34.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They actually took power from the power grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:34.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们实际上是从电网上获取电力
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:37.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But they sustained this reaction
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:37.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但他们维持这个反应
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:39.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and they were able to take the materials out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:39.95,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们能够采取的材料出来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:42.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,reprocess them, extract the plutonium
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:42.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,重新处理它们 提取钚
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:46.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and that was the material was used to make the trinity device
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:46.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这些材料被用来制造三位一体装置
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which was the first atom bomb ever detonated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是有史以来引爆的第一颗原子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.90,0:04:52.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And of course later the fat man which was dropped over Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.90,0:04:52.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然 后来在长崎上空投放的胖子也是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:58.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So with plutonium yeah the 239 is the stuff that explodes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:58.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 对于钚来说 239是爆炸的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:03.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but as it turns out the other isotopes pretty much all explode too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:03.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但事实证明 其他同位素也几乎都会爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:10.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,However with a material in the reactor it's not just plutonium-239 you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:10.06,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然而 对于反应堆中的材料 你得到的不仅仅是钚239
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:14.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You get other isotopes produced because you can't exactly control the series of reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:14.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你会得到其他同位素的产生 因为你不能完全控制一系列的反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.80,0:05:19.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Sometimes that 239 will absorb another neutron and it'll become plutonium-240.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.80,0:05:19.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有时 239会吸收另一个中子 变成钚-240
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:23.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Sometimes there are other reactions that will produce plutonium-238
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:23.42,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有时还有其他反应 会产生钚238
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:27.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is the stuff that is used in spacecraft for power generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:27.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是在航天器中用于发电的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.67,0:05:31.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The problem is that both of these materials have drawbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.67,0:05:31.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,问题是 这两种材料都有缺点
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.89,0:05:38.13,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The plutonium-240 is just as valid as a weapons material
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.89,0:05:38.13,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,钚-240作为一种武器材料同样有效
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:41.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but it will undergo spontaneous fission more often
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:41.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但它会更经常地发生自发裂变
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:45.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and that means that it can trigger the reaction early.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:45.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而这意味着它可以提前触发反应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.39,0:05:48.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And I don't mean early as in when the bombs are sitting around doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.39,0:05:48.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而我的意思不是指在炸弹无所事事时的早期
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:53.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I mean that during the process of collapsing your material down into a critical mass
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:53.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 在把你的材料压缩成一个临界质量的过程中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:55.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,you want to squish it as small as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:55.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你想把它压得越小越好
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:05:58.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it takes a finite amount of time to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:05:58.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并且需要有限的时间来做到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:01.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But if you've got too much plutonium-240 there
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:01.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是 如果你有太多的钚-240在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.52,0:06:05.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it can actually trigger the reaction while you are still squeezing things down
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.52,0:06:05.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它实际上可以触发反应 而你仍然在挤压的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.84,0:06:11.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and that means you never reach your peak density and the bomb explodes with less energy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.84,0:06:11.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着你永远不会达到你的峰值密度 炸弹爆炸的能量较小
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.88,0:06:13.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because it has less new density.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.88,0:06:13.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为它的新密度较小
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:15.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So that's one problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:15.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这就是一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:18.41,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The plutonium 240 by the way is the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:18.41,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,顺便说一下 钚240的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.49,0:06:21.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,why they couldn't build a simple gun type device
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.49,0:06:21.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,为什么他们不能建立一个简单的枪型装置
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:26.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,where you shoot one slug into another and that makes your critical mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:26.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你把一个弹头射入另一个弹头 这就是你的临界质量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:29.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,With that they figured out the barrel needed to be way too long
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:29.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,有了这个 他们发现枪管需要太长了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:33.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because plutonium's chance of predetonation was too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:33.33,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为钚的预爆机会太高
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:41.09,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So with weapons grades plutonium you make sure there's no more than 6.5% plutonium-240.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.28,0:06:41.09,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 对于武器级钚 你要确保其含量不超过6.5%的钚-240
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:45.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The 238 as I said is used in spacecraft because it's radioactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:45.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,正如我所说 238被用于航天器 因为它具有放射性
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:46.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It generates a lot of heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:46.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它产生了大量的热量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.30,0:06:51.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So having too much heat in the device that you want to use is probably a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.30,0:06:51.15,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 在你想使用的设备中 有太多的热量可能是一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:53.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It means you have to somehow get rid of that heat
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:53.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着你必须以某种方式摆脱这种热量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:56.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,or it will damage components damage your explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:56.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,否则就会损坏部件 损坏你的炸药
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:03.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So the weapons grade material has less than one half of a% of plutonium-238 in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:03.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 武器级材料中的钚238含量不到一半
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:10.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So that's your thing 93% plutonium-239 with 7% other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:10.99,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 这是你的东西93％的钚239和7％的其他东西
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:12.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That's weapons grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:12.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这就是武器级
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:16.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But again that's just what is easy to work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:16.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这也只是容易处理的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:22.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,As you get more and more other isotopes in there it is still possible to build weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:22.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当你得到越来越多的其他同位素在那里 它仍然有可能建立武器
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.34,0:07:25.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and in 1962 Britain was working with the US
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.34,0:07:25.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,1962年 英国与美国合作
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.78,0:07:29.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and they came along with some reactor grade material that had
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.78,0:07:29.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们带来了一些反应堆级的材料 其中有
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.91,0:07:33.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but it's believed it was about 15% other isotopes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.91,0:07:33.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但据说有大约15%的其他同位素
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:38.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and they used that to build a bomb to demonstrate that was possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:38.21,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们用它来制造炸弹 以证明这是可能的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:39.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:39.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它是的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:43.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It was a little weaker I believe it was only about 10 kilotons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.93,0:07:43.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它有点弱 我相信它只有大约10千吨
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:44.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But this is all classified.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:44.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这都是机密
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The exact numbers here are totally classified.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这里的确切数字是完全保密的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:50.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And I'm just guessing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:50.29,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而我只是在这里猜测
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:52.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So it is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:52.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以它是可能的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:56.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I think there's another calculation I saw that said that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:56.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我想我看到的另一个计算方法是 说
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.22,0:08:05.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,going from like 5% other isotopes to 15% other isotopes cuts your weapon yield by a factor of 10
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.22,0:08:05.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,从5%的其他同位素到15%的其他同位素 使你的武器产量减少10倍
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:09.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then going from 15% to 25% cuts it by another factor of 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:09.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后从15%增加到25% 再减少10个系数
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:11.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But that's not to say that it's impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:11.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这并不是说这是不可能的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:14.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it just gets harder and your yields get lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:14.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它只是变得更难 你的产量变得更低
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.34,0:08:19.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So the thing about making the plutonium in the reactor is that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.34,0:08:19.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 关于在反应堆中制造钚的事情是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:22.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because you've got all these other side reactions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:22.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为你有所有这些其他的副反应
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:27.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,reactors are designed to make fuel or fissile material for nuclear weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.86,0:08:27.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,反应堆的设计是为了制造核武器的燃料或裂变材料
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.14,0:08:32.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,will generally only keep the rods in the reactor for a couple of weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.14,0:08:32.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,通常只在反应堆中保留几个星期的棒子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:34.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then take them out for reprocessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:34.43,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后把它们拿出来进行再加工
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:38.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But that in many reactor designs pressurized water designs means
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:38.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是 在许多反应堆设计中 压水设计意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:42.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,shutting the entire reactor down letting it cool down and then taking the rods out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:42.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,关闭整个反应堆 让它冷却下来 然后把棒子拿出来
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.74,0:08:48.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Whereas the reactors that were used to generate the plutonium for the first weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.74,0:08:48.14,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而用于产生第一种武器的钚的反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.39,0:08:52.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,they had this sort of continuous flow system where you pushed the rods in at one end
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.39,0:08:52.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们有这种连续流动的系统 你把棒子从一端推进去
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.41,0:08:56.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it was horizontal and as you pushed it in it pushed the rods out the back
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.41,0:08:56.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它是水平的 当你把它推入 它把棒子从后面推出来
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:09:01.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so they could keep the fuel in the reactor for only a limited amount of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:09:01.57,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 他们可以保持燃料在反应堆中只有有限的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.32,0:09:05.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,When you have the fuel sitting in the reactor for years
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.32,0:09:05.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当你把燃料放在反应堆里好几年的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.75,0:09:09.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it generates much much more of these other reactants
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.75,0:09:09.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它产生了更多的这些其他反应物
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:12.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and so the material is not considered weapons grade
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:12.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 该材料不被认为是武器级
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:14.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,unless you can somehow remove these.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:14.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,除非你能以某种方式消除这些
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:20.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So yeah that's again why you want to control reprocess nuclear material
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:20.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以 这也是为什么你要控制核材料的再加工
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but equally it becomes very hard to build an atom bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但同样地 制造原子弹也变得非常困难
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because of the problems of pre-detonation and heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为有预爆炸和热量的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.36,0:09:30.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now there is one other nuclear material that's worth mentioning
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.36,0:09:30.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在还有一种值得一提的核材料
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:33.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and that is uranium-233.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:33.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那就是铀233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:38.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That's another isotope o'f uranium that in many ways is actually better than uranium-235.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:38.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是另一种铀的同位素 在许多方面实际上比铀235更好
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:42.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You actually need a lower critical mass of uranium-233.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:42.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你实际上需要一个较低临界质量的铀233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.74,0:09:46.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So uranium-233 comes from thorium reactors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.74,0:09:46.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 铀233来自于钍反应堆
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:51.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,When thorium-232 which is the most common isotope absorbs a neutron
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.60,0:09:51.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当钍-232（最常见的同位素）吸收了一个中子后
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it transmutes into uranium-233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它转化为铀-233
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:58.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and then that's the stuff that actually undergoes fission in these reactors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:58.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,然后这就是在这些反应堆中实际发生裂变的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.06,0:10:02.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And again yeah you can use this in bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.06,0:10:02.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,再说一遍 你可以在炸弹中使用这个
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:05.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It was been tested. The US has tested a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:05.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它已经被测试过了 美国已经测试了一种武器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:07.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I believe India might have tested a weapon with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:07.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我相信印度可能已经用它试验了一种武器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:12.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The problem is that again it's a material produced in a reactor
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:12.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,问题是 这也是一种在反应堆中产生的材料
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.43,0:10:16.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you have other materials other isotopes produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.43,0:10:16.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且你还有其他材料和其他同位素的生产
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:21.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the biggest problem is uranium-232 that can result
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:21.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,最大的问题是可能产生铀-232
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:24.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and on its own it's fine right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:24.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而它本身是好的 对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.64,0:10:26.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It'll actually undergo fission too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.64,0:10:26.06,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它实际上也会发生裂变
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.43,0:10:30.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But it decays into a whole bunch of other decay products
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.43,0:10:30.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但它会衰变成一大堆其他衰变产物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.11,0:10:33.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which produce a lot of gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.11,0:10:33.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这产生了大量的伽马射线
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:40.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And so I believe anything more than about 50 parts per million of uranium-232 in your sample
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:40.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以我相信 如果你的样品中铀-232的含量超过百万分之五十 就很难进行处理
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:44.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,makes it very hard to work with because of the amount of gamma radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:44.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,就很难处理 因为有大量的伽马辐射
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:50.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You have to move to like shielded glove box or remote manipulation rather than simply glove boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.20,0:10:50.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你必须转移到像屏蔽的手套箱或远程操作 而不是简单的手套箱
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:54.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So this 50 parts per million requirement is really hard to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:54.53,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这个百万分之五十的要求真的很难实现
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.85,0:10:59.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it's one of the reasons why thorium reactors are usually cited by their proponents
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.85,0:10:59.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这也是钍反应堆的支持者通常将其列为扩散风险很低的原因之一
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:03.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,as being a very low proliferation risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:03.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,作为一个非常低的扩散风险
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:07.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So yeah that's that's what weapons grade means.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:07.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以 是的 这就是武器级的含义
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:10.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's all about the isotope ratios of all these different materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:10.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这都是关于所有这些不同材料的同位素比率
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:16.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There's probably other fissile materials where the concept of weapons grade has been considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:16.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,可能还有其他裂变材料也被认为是武器级的概念
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.97,0:11:23.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You can make a bomb with neptunium, californium, americium. I had never had to know how to pronounce that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.97,0:11:23.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你可以用镎、锎、镅制作炸弹 我从来没有必要知道如何发音
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:26.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But it's a thing that makes stuff explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:26.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但它是一种能让东西爆炸的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:29.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So yes now you all know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:29.51,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以是的 现在你们都知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.51,0:11:33.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Weapons grade material. Make sure you've got your percentages laid out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.51,0:11:33.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,武器级材料 请确保你已经得到了你的百分比
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:36.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Otherwise you won't get the boom boom that you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:36.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,否则 你不会得到你想要的轰鸣声
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.39,0:11:38.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.39,0:11:38.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我是斯科特-曼利 飞行安全
